-- Obama Re-Election Groups Raise $43.6 Million in April
-- B y   H a n s   N i c h o l s
-- 2012-05-16T10:26:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/obama-re-election-groups-raise-43-6-million-in-april.html
President  Barack Obama ’s re-election
effort raised more than $43.6 million in April, the campaign
announced in a Twitter message this morning.  The campaign said it collected money from 437,323 people,
including 169,500 first-time donors, in April. The average
donation was $50.23, the campaign said.  “This election is going to be close,” campaign manager
Jim Messina said in a YouTube video linked to the Twitter
posting.  To contact the reporter on this story:
